Thursdays are an acquired taste.

@Jon Mark 

If they do it again, you'll nail it.

I don't in general believe that whatever doesn't kill you makes you stronger, but I do believe that whatever learning experience is the most painful will be the most remembered, and most inoculated against.

@MFSTEVE 

I went to a party earlier this month that was billed as a fête (for alliteration with "fifty"), so I plunked it in immediately while simultaneously assuming it couldn't possibly be the answer! 

Fête is French for party (thank you, high school language requirements) but is also a loan word in English.

@HEK 

You TAKE the NE out of FAR GONE and give it to SEATTLE to get SEA (NE)TTLE, which fits the clue [Stinging jellyfish].

It works just like the three other theme answer pairs.

@Sarah 

Think of it as HEADS TO.  It makes sense as a part of a phrase.

There's probably more to say about it, and I'm guessing we'll see some for complete replies.

@Sarah 

